 l ABS latest release page\n\nExplainer:\n• What it is: Producer Price 
 Index\n\n• Measures: Change in prices received by producers for goods 
 and services.\n\n• Usual market effect: Higher-than-forecast PPI can b
 e bullish for the local currency if traders expect producer inflation to
  flow through to consumer inflation.\n\n• Why traders care: PPI can pr
 ovide an early signal of inflation pressure before it reaches consumers.
 \n\n• Frequency: Monthly in the US. Quarterly in Australia.\n\n• Not
 es: PPI is usually less market-moving than CPI\, but it can still matter
  when inflation is the main macro theme.\n\n• Acronyms: PPI = Producer
  Price Index.\n\nOfficial source: https://www.abs.gov.au/statistics/econ
 omy/price-indexes-and-inflation/producer-price-indexes-australia/mar-202
