 l ABS latest release page\n\nExplainer:\n• What it is: Wage Price Inde
 x / Average Earnings\n\n• Measures: Change in wages and earnings.\n\n
 • Usual market effect: Higher-than-forecast wage growth can be bullish
  for the local currency if traders expect stronger inflation pressure an
 d tighter central-bank policy.\n\n• Why traders care: Wage growth can 
 feed into inflation and is closely watched by central banks.\n\n• Freq
 uency: Monthly or quarterly depending on release.\n\n• Notes: Strong w
 ages can be positive for consumers but can also increase inflation press
 ure.\n\n• Acronyms: WPI = Wage Price Index.\n\nOfficial source: https:
 //www.abs.gov.au/statistics/economy/price-indexes-and-inflation/wage-pri
 ce-index-australia/mar-2026\n\nExplainer:\n• What it is: Wage Price In
