 nd tighter central-bank policy.\n\n• Why traders care: Wage growth can
  feed into inflation and is closely watched by central banks.\n\n• Fre
 quency: Monthly or quarterly depending on release.\n\n• Notes: Strong 
 wages can be positive for consumers but can also increase inflation pres
 sure.\n\n• Acronyms: WPI = Wage Price Index.\n\nOfficial source: https
 ://www.abs.gov.au/statistics/economy/price-indexes-and-inflation/wage-pr
 ice-index-australia/mar-2026\n\nExplainer:\n• What it is: Wage Price I
