  AU ABS\nImpact: high\nOfficial ABS series page release date. Time zone 
 shown by ABS: AEST.\n\nExplainer:\n• What it is: Consumer Price Index\
 n\n• Measures: Change in the prices paid by consumers for a basket of 
 goods and services.\n\n• Usual market effect: Higher-than-forecast inf
 lation is usually bullish for the local currency and bearish for bonds\,
  because markets may price in higher interest rates.\n\n• Why traders 
 care: CPI is one of the most watched inflation indicators because it can
  quickly shift central-bank rate expectations.\n\n• Frequency: US CPI 
 is monthly. Australian CPI has both monthly indicator releases and quart
 erly CPI releases.\n\n• Notes: Core CPI removes volatile items such as
  food and energy to give a cleaner read on underlying inflation pressure
 .\n\n• Acronyms: CPI = Consumer Price Index.\n\nOfficial source: https
