SUMMARY:🔥 US Fed: FOMC Interest Rate Decision
DESCRIPTION:Source: US Fed\nImpact: high\nSource: US Fed\nImpact: high\nS
 ource: US Fed\nImpact: high\nSource: US Fed\nImpact: high\nSource: US Fe
 d\nImpact: high\nSource: US Fed\nImpact: high\nSource: US Fed\nImpact: h
 igh\nSource: US Fed\nImpact: high\nSource: US Fed\nImpact: high\nSource:
  US Fed\nImpact: high\nOfficial Federal Reserve monthly calendar FOMC me
 eting entry.\n\nExplainer:\n• What it is: Central Bank Rate Decision\n
 \n• Measures: Interest-rate decision\, policy statement and guidance f
 rom the central bank.\n\n• Usual market effect: More hawkish-than-expe
 cted guidance is usually bullish for the local currency and bearish for 
 bonds. More dovish-than-expected guidance is usually bearish for the cur
 rency and bullish for bonds.\n\n• Why traders care: Central-bank decis
 ions directly affect interest rates\, currency valuation\, bond yields a
 nd equity risk appetite.\n\n• Frequency: Scheduled several times per y
 ear.\n\n• Notes: The market often reacts not only to the rate decision
 \, but also to the statement\, forecasts\, press conference and tone.\n\
 n• Acronyms: FOMC = Federal Open Market Committee\; RBA = Reserve Bank
  of Australia.\n\nOfficial source: https://www.federalreserve.gov/newsev
 ents/2026-july.htm\n\nExplainer:\n• What it is: Central Bank Rate Deci
 sion\n\n• Measures: Interest-rate decision\, policy statement and guid
 ance from the central bank.\n\n• Usual market effect: More hawkish-tha
 n-expected guidance is usually bullish for the local currency and bearis
 h for bonds. More dovish-than-expected guidance is usually bearish for t
 he currency and bullish for bonds.\n\n• Why traders care: Central-bank
  decisions directly affect interest rates\, currency valuation\, bond yi
 elds and equity risk appetite.\n\n• Frequency: Scheduled several times
  per year.\n\n• Notes: The market often reacts not only to the rate de
 cision\, but also to the statement\, forecasts\, press conference and to
 ne.\n\n• Acronyms: FOMC = Federal Open Market Committee\; RBA = Reserv
 e Bank of Australia.\n\nOfficial source: https://www.federalreserve.gov/
 newsevents/2026-july.htm\n\nExplainer:\n• What it is: Central Bank Rat
 e Decision\n\n• Measures: Interest-rate decision\, policy statement an
 d guidance from the central bank.\n\n• Usual market effect: More hawki
 sh-than-expected guidance is usually bullish for the local currency and 
 bearish for bonds. More dovish-than-expected guidance is usually bearish
  for the currency and bullish for bonds.\n\n• Why traders care: Centra
 l-bank decisions directly affect interest rates\, currency valuation\, b
 ond yields and equity risk appetite.\n\n• Frequency: Scheduled several
  times per year.\n\n• Notes: The market often reacts not only to the r
 ate decision\, but also to the statement\, forecasts\, press conference 
 and tone.\n\n• Acronyms: FOMC = Federal Open Market Committee\; RBA = 
 Reserve Bank of Australia.\n\nOfficial source: https://www.federalreserv
 e.gov/newsevents/2026-july.htm\n\nExplainer:\n• What it is: Central Ba
 nk Rate Decision\n\n• Measures: Interest-rate decision\, policy statem
